we use At command to create a one time job

# To schedule a job we need to know time so we use
$ date
$ at HH:MM and <EOT> 				# install at if not installed, <EOT> end of transition , ctrl + d
$ at MM:DD:YY and then ctrl+D

we can also do

$ at now + 5 minutes  

# List all at jobs
$ atq		or
$ at -l

# Cancel all scheduled jobs
$ atrm 2 3 		# 2 and 3 is job id's
